President Donald J. Trump will award the Presidential Medal of Freedom to Louis Leo Holtz, recognizing him as one of the greatest football coaches of all time. Holtz has also made contributions as a philanthropist, author, and American patriot. He served in the United States Army Reserves for seven years after graduating from Kent State University. Holtz had a successful coaching career, leading teams such as the University of Notre Dame to national championships. After retiring from coaching, he authored books, worked as a sports analyst, and established two charities. Holtz has received numerous honors and accolades for his accomplishments both on and off the football field.